$answer= Compute("x >= -2.5");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML a. Use the graph of [` y = 30 - 8x `] above to solve the inequality
[``` 30 - 8x \le 50 ```]
Answer: [_]{$answer}{8}
Note: Use "[`\delimitershortfall-1sp\newcommand\abs[1]{\left|#1\right|}\newcommand{\lt}{<} \lt= `]" for the [` \le `] symbol, and use "[`\newcommand{\gt}{>} \gt= `]" for [` \ge \text{.}`]
a. Solve the inequality algebraically.
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. As we found in the previous Checkpoint, the point on [`y=30-8x`] where [` y=50 `] occurs when [` x=-2.5 \text{.}`] The [` y `]-coordinates are smaller as we move to the right on the graph, that is, for the points where [` x\ge -2.5 \text{.}`]
a. [$NBSP]*
[```\newcommand{\blert}[1]{\boldsymbol{\color{blue}{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} 30-8x \amp \le 50 \amp\amp\blert{{\small \text{Subtract 30 from both sides.}}} \\ -8x \amp \le 20 \amp\amp \blert{{\small \text{Divide by } {-8} \text{ and reverse inequality.}}} \\ x \amp \ge -2.5 \end{aligned} ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
